Description:
Verilator revision befb415, but the bug affects all v5 versions and some earlier ones.
Test case:
// verilator lint_off MULTIDRIVEN
module t(input clk);
  initial begin
    $dumpfile("dump.vcd");
    $dumpvars;
  end

  logic [31:0] lhs1, lhs2, rhs;

  always_comb lhs1 = rhs;
  assign lhs2 = rhs;

  always @(posedge clk) rhs = '1;

  always @(negedge clk) begin
    release lhs1;
    release lhs2;
  end
endmodule
Waveform:

lhs1 and lhs2 are oscillating for some reason, when they should equal rhs.
The always_comb bug also appears on v4.228.

This seems to be causing a regression in Caliptra: chipsalliance/caliptra-rtl#79
